1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:25,000
What if the path through the wall was visible? Not the jobs — the wall.
Five offices, forty-seven forms, a bus that takes seventy-one minutes.

2
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:50,000
GoWork is a workforce navigator. It maps the wall — every barrier
between a worker and a paycheck — and routes them around it.

3
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:15,000
We're going to walk through one resident's twelve weeks in Fort Worth.
Carlos is twenty-nine. A father of one. Four years of warehouse work.

4
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:30,000
He has three hundred dollars and no car. He is ready to work.
This is The Wall.

5
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Fort Worth, Texas. Carlos lives east of downtown. ZIP 76119.
Trinity Metro routes thread the city — half don't reach the warehouses.

6
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Single father of one daughter, four years old. Three years past a
misdemeanor — sentence complete. Forklift certified. Four barriers.

7
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Most workforce sites pretend barriers don't matter. We do the math.
Criminal record: 71-minute commute. No childcare: $1,200 a month.
Bad credit: 540 score, one in three jobs unreachable.

8
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Five offices. Forty-seven forms. Each one says go to the next one.
Without GoWork, this is the path. We named it so we could replace it.

9
00:02:42,000 --> 00:03:05,000
When more pay means less money. A two-dollar raise sounds like a win.
Childcare subsidy gone at $14/hr. SNAP gone at $17/hr.

10
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:25,000
Five stops. Twelve weeks. One plan. Home to DPS to HHSC to Legal Aid
to Workforce Solutions. Trinity Metro Bus 4 and Bus 6 carry him.

11
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:55,000
The wall isn't a list. It's a graph. Thirty-three nodes. Seven
categories. Resolve one barrier and three others move within reach.

12
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:08,000
It works in Fort Worth. It will work in Montgomery. It will work
where you are. Two cities deployed. Six on deck. Same engine.

13
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:15,000
You've seen the wall. You've seen the labyrinth. Now skip both —
start your assessment.

14
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:30,000
GoWork is open-source under MIT. Fort Worth is the reference
deployment. Montgomery is the second. Built for HackFW 2026.
